The paper deals with active learning, semi-supervised learning, and optimization using submodular functions. These topics are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses more on the theoretical aspects of the problem, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
